<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- M0-M2: Sparse, modal Em atmosphere — 2-note open 5ths in both hands. Pattern "44" quartal
  (P4+P5 = E-B-E and B-F#-B etc.) gives the Dorian/Aeolian modal sound befitting
  "The King Shall Come" Advent expectancy text.
- M3: Ascending sequence Am→Bm→Em→D — each beat a new chord with stepwise bass motion
  A2→B2→E3→D3. Pattern "33" (root pos 3rds) in RH tracking melody thirds.
- M4: I (G) arrival — quartal RH (G4-D5, P4+P4) for an open, "crown" quality.
  Full I root pos LH.
- M5: Am7 color at beat 3 — LH uses "333" pattern (A-E-G-C) with the added 7th (G).
  This is the most harmonically rich moment before the final descent.
- M6-M7: Descent and re-ascent. M6 V→Em descent, M7 Em→V→I→Bm rising arc.
- M8: Em conclusive — 3-note RH spread, LH spans E2-B3 (full modal close).

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- LH bass line across M1-M3: E3→B2→E3→A2→B2→E3→D3 (vi-iii-vi-ii-iii-vi-V stepwise descent).
- Inner voice C4 (ii chord top) appears M5 beat 2-3, then resolves B3 in M5 beat 4 (I chord).
- Suspension in M4: RH holds D5 across beats 1-4 (dotted half); acts as 5th of I, then 3rd
  of I inversion at beat 4 — a subtle pedal point effect.
- M7 beat 2-3: contrary motion — RH F#4-A4-D5 (V ascends D5) against LH D3→G2 (V descends).

TEXTURE ARC:
- Pickup-M2: Very sparse, 2-note open 5ths. Modal, ancient, expectant.
- M3: Movement — ascending bass line with matching thirds in RH.
- M4: Bright I arrival — sustained, full resonance. The "king comes" moment.
- M5-M6: Color and descent — Am7, flowing RH, dropping to low B3.
- M7 (climax): 3-note RH, 4-note LH, every beat changes — maximum density.
- M8: Open, resonant final Em — wide spacing, modal close.
-->
